{'message': 'Thank you for sharing your experience with us, Rice. We are sorry to hear that you were not satisfied with the number of flowers in your St. John’s Wort. While this lot does contain a good number of buds and flowering heads, they can definitely blend into the chopped leaves, making them hard to differentiate. It is also important to note that while the phenolic compounds are still present in dried St. John’s Wort, they are only photoreactive and turn red when the fresh plant is used in infusions. That said, matters of quality are extremely important to us, and we always want to know if anything is amiss!

I am glad to see that you have already been in touch with our Claims & Returns Team. They will reach out to you directly to assist you in getting this matter straightened out.  Warmly ~ Celeste

', 'publishedDate': '2024-03-25T22:08:22.000Z', 'updatedDate': '2024-03-25T22:09:16.000Z'}

{'message': 'Thank you for taking the time to share your feedback with us! We are sorry to hear that some of the products you are looking for have not been available. Unfortunately, the procurement of natural goods is sometimes unpredictable due to things like weather or crop success, to name a few. When items do arrive at our facility, they are subject to our rigorous quality control process in order to make sure we only provide the best herbal products to our customers. If they do not meet our standards, the product is rejected and we must begin the sourcing process again. For these reasons, a backorder system is not a viable option for us at this time.

In regard to our shipping costs, we aim to be as transparent as possible with our customers every step of the way. We understand the appeal of free shipping, but what most do not see is that companies that offer free shipping often have to find ways to recoup those costs and do so by raising product prices. We have chosen to give our customers this information upfront rather than to incorporate it into the cost of our products.

We hope this helps to better explain our ordering and shipping processes and greatly appreciate your continued support. Best wishes ~ Erin ', 'publishedDate': '2024-04-01T19:54:09.000Z', 'updatedDate': None}

{'message': "Hello, Cardesha. We're sorry to hear that you have been dissatisfied with our customer support timeframe. We did receive your initial review 2 hours ago and sent you a reply within an hour to explain the next steps. Our Claims & Returns Team has been made aware that you have been displeased with one of the items you received and they will be following up with you directly to learn more about the experience you described in your first review. 

We also looked to see if you had reached out through email, chat, or phone and we have not been able to find other correspondence that is awaiting reply. If you did reach out, we would love to know more about that so we can look into that further.  

We welcome you to email us (support@mountainroseherbs.com), call us (800-879-3337), or utilize the live chat feature on our website if you have any further questions or concerns. Otherwise, our Claims and Returns team will be happy to assist you shortly.  Best ~ Erin", 'publishedDate': '2024-04-03T21:51:10.000Z', 'updatedDate': None}

{'message': 'Thank you for reaching out and sharing your feedback, Tara! It is great to hear that you have been enjoying the quality of our products. We are sorry that the cost of shipping to Hawaii has been higher than you would like. Rates to Hawaii are calculated, in part, based on the weight of the order, but the distance is a factor as well. We utilize FedEx’s live rates for shipping outside of the contiguous 48 states, which we then discount by 30 percent. Because they are live rates, however, they do fluctuate and reflect current transportation costs.

Regarding our back-in-stock notifications, we recommend regularly checking junk and spam folders for these types of emails as they are commonly mis-sorted by our customers’ email service providers. Additionally, we recommend signing up for alerts for all size options, as the notifications are dependent on the selection that has been made when entering your email. For example, you have a back-in-stock notification requested for Calendula Flowers. We currently have Calendula Flowers in stock, however, because of limited availability, we only have the 4 oz size available. Your notification was requested for the 1 lb size and since this size has not been available for some time, no notification has been triggered. Entering your email address under both sizes helps to avoid this.

We certainly appreciate your continued support and hope that this helps to explain some of the issues you have been experiencing. Wishing you a happy Spring! ~ Erin', 'publishedDate': '2024-04-08T17:06:05.000Z', 'updatedDate': None}

{'message': 'Thank you for your kind words, William! We are happy to hear you have enjoyed the quality of our organic offerings. 

As for shipping, we understand that it has become commonplace for online shoppers not to see shipping charges, but the truth is that many companies just include these costs by raising product prices or charging subscription fees. We have opted for a more transparent approach to our pricing structure. 

We do offer a discounted flat-rate shipping option for orders shipped to physical addresses in the contiguous 48 states and I do see that you have chosen this option on past orders. The first tier covers orders weighing up to 4.99 lbs., and the next tier covers up to 19.99 lbs. Many of our customers place larger orders less frequently or place group orders with friends and family to get the most out of those shipping costs. We hope this helps to better explain our approach to shipping and sincerely appreciate your continued support! Warmly ~ Celeste', 'publishedDate': '2024-04-16T19:38:46.000Z', 'updatedDate': None}

{'message': 'Thank you for your review, Jennifer. We are sorry to hear that our shipping time and cost were not what you expected. Here at Mountain Rose Herbs, we do take a little extra time to fill our orders. We pour our herbs in small batches based on our customers’ ordering needs and hand-pack all orders carefully. While this attention to detail may add a day or two to fulfillment times, we are proud of this personal touch.

We will always provide a fulfillment estimate prior to checkout so our customers can decide what works best for them. I can see that your order left us in 4 days, which was in line with the estimate provided. Your package only spent 3 days in transit, as well, which is even faster than what we are used to seeing for orders that are going to the East Coast. Should you ever need it, we do offer expedited shipping options for qualifying orders. This can be a great choice for those times when you need your order to arrive a little faster.

As for the cost of shipping, we have maintained the lowest rates possible while remaining transparent about these costs. Our flat rate tiers, which are available to customers shipping to a physical address within the contiguous 48 states, allow us to offer discounted rates without having to subsidize the cost of shipping with increased product prices. If you ever have questions about our current fulfillment, shipping estimates, or expedited shipping options, feel free to reach out to our Customer Service Team directly and we will be happy to help! Best, ~ Erin', 'publishedDate': '2024-04-23T17:41:47.000Z', 'updatedDate': None}

